						<summary>

						<p>On a broken slab set up in the Māruti temple.</p>						

						<p>[Vikramāditya VI], 1105-06 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the 19th regnal year, perhaps of Tribhuvanamalla and Pārthiva, the other details being lost. This date corresponds to 1105-06 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a gift of land and house-site to the god Mūlasthāna. The epigraph is mutilated.</p>						

						</summary>
